msgid ""
"[skull]: -X. X is half the number of revealed locations (rounded down)."
"[cultist]: -2. If you fail and your location is fully flooded, take 1 damage."
"[tablet]: -4. If you fail, place 1 of your clues on your location."
"[elder_thing]: -3 (-5 instead if your location is not flooded)."
msgstr ""
"[skull]：–X。X为已揭示地点数量的一半(向下取整)。"
"[cultist]：–2。如果你检定失败且你所在地点完全淹没，受到1点伤害。"
"[tablet]：–4。如果你检定失败，将你的1个线索放到你所在地点。"
"[elder_thing]：–3(如果你所在地点未淹没，改为–5)。"

msgid ""
"[skull]: -X. X is the number of revealed locations."
"[cultist]: -3. If your location is flooded, take 1 damage."
"[tablet]: -4. For each point you fail by, place 1 of your clues on your location."
"[elder_thing]: -4 (-6 instead if your location is not flooded)."
msgstr ""
"[skull]：–X。X为已揭示的地点数。"
"[cultist]：–3。如果你所在地点已淹没，受到1点伤害。"
"[tablet]：–4。你检定失败且每低于难度1点，将你的1个线索放到你所在地点。"
"[elder_thing]：–4（如果你所在地点未淹没，改为–6）。"

msgid "Location Adjacency in The Drowned Quarter"
msgstr "溺亡城区中的地点相邻关系"

msgid "The sound of crackling electricity greets you as you enter the undersea dome. Flooded trenches and crumbling ruins cover the round plaza on the seafloor. Try as you might, your eyes keep drifting to the ocean beyond the alien barrier. A bloom of jellyfish floats dreamily through the tenebrous depths. If the energy field were to disappear for any reason, the expedition would surely be swept away."
msgstr "你走进海底穹顶的时候，居然听到了噼啪的电流声。海底的圆广场上全是被淹没的沟渠和崩塌的废墟。你费尽心力，目光还是不断飘向异星屏障上方的海洋。一团水母浮过阴暗的深海，如梦如幻。要是能量场莫名消失，那整个探险队肯定都会被卷入涡流。"

msgid ""
"“I think this is the source,” Andy points to the round structure in the center of the plaza. Bolts of electricity lick the shimmering bubble above. The structure is the source of the glow and, presumably, the energy field protecting these ruins from the ocean water. Inside, you find a spinning orrery: a complex mechanism of hovering spheres and whirring gears that stir a constant electric current. Locked at its core is an incandescent orb. Andy fidgets nervously. “It’s powering the machine. I don’t know what’ll happen if we take it out but… it looks like something Mr. Tillinghast would want.”"
"Before you can object, he sets to operating the ancient controls. There may be a way to remove the orb without drowning…"
msgstr ""
"“我想这里就是源头。”安迪指着广场中央的圆形结构说道，那里的电流掠过上面闪亮的泡泡。可能就是这个光源发射出了保护海底废墟的能量场。你看到里面有个圆形的太阳系仪：这个复杂的机械由旋转的球体和嗡嗡的齿轮构成，正不断发射着电流，核心位置则固定着一个炽热发光的球体。安迪紧张地动来动去：“它在为整个装置供能。我不知道要是拿出来会怎么样…但它看上去会是蒂林哈斯特先生想要的东西。”"
"你还没来得及阻止，他就开始操作古代装置了。也许有办法能在不淹死的前提下拿走球体……"

msgid ""
"You follow the expedition past pits of deep water and sunken ruins to the source of the glow and, presumably, the energy field. Inside it, you find a spinning orrery: a complex mechanism of hovering spheres and whirring gears that stir a constant electric current. Locked at its core is an incandescent orb. Ruby gasps. “It’s some kind of pumping station. I’d wager that orb is an important part of it. It’s possible that stealing it could bring the ocean down on our heads.” She smiles rakishly. “So you’d better be ready to run.”"
"Before you can object, she sets to operating the ancient controls. There may be a way to take the orb without drowning…"
msgstr ""
"你跟着探险队经过深水坑和沉没的废墟，这里就是光源，可能也是能量场的来源。你看到里面有个圆形的太阳系仪：这个复杂的机械由旋转的球体和嗡嗡的齿轮构成，正不断发射着电流，核心位置则固定着一个炽热发光的球体。露比倒抽一口凉气：“这是某种泵，我敢打赌金属球是其中重要的一部分。要是拿走它，整个海洋可能都会倒在我们头上。”她俏皮地笑了，“所以你最好准备快跑。”"
"你还没来得及阻止，她就开始操作古代装置了。也许有办法能在不淹死的前提下拿走球体……"

msgid "If an investigator has the \"No Place Like Home\" task:"
msgstr "如果调查员有“吾家可归”任务："

msgid "Task: No Place Like Home"
msgstr "任务：吾家可归"

msgid ""
"Your head spins as you look up at the alien orrery. The sight brings you back to that first night, the night Tillinghast took you off the streets. The stars that night were bright, and you can't forget their particular formation, the same formation in front of you now. Away from the constant grind and concerns of your life in Arkham, you've done some thinking. Tillinghast's words were kind, but his tone was harsh, cold, unfeeling. Reflecting on it, you have only garnered the businessman's attention when you were useful. There was no kindness in his act, when he saved you, he acquired you as yet another lackey in his quiver of debtors."
"This is the umpteenth \"last job\" you've been on. Is Tillinghast really worth his word?"
msgstr ""
"你望着异星而来的天体仪器，一阵头晕目眩。这一幕让你想到了一切开始的晚上，蒂林哈斯特把你从街头捞走的那个晚上。那夜星光明亮，而你也忘不了群星的排列，就和你面前的一模一样。远离了阿卡姆的不断奔波和蝇营狗苟，你终于能停下来思考一番。蒂林哈斯特的话术客气，但腔调却是生硬、冰冷、无情。回想起来，你好像只在有用的时候才吸引到这个生意人的注意。他的举止并无善意；他救你的时候，只是想着用债务再给自己招一个狗腿子罢了。"
"这已经是第无数次“最后一件活”了。蒂林哈斯特当真言而有信吗?"

msgid "<i>\"Mr. Tillinghast has treated me well. I trust him.\"</i>"
msgstr "<i>“蒂林哈斯特先生待我不薄。我相信他。”</i>"

msgid "Heal 1 mental or 1 physical trauma from your investigator. Erase 1 progress under \"No Place Like Home\" in your Campaign Log."
msgstr "治愈你调查员的1点精神创伤或1点肉体创伤。在剧本日志中，“吾家可归”下擦去1进展。"

msgid "<i>\"I'm on my own. There's no one I can trust.\"</i>"
msgstr "<i>“我就靠自己。别人都不能信任。</i>”"

msgid "Mark 2 progress under \"No Place Like Home\" in your Campaign Log and suffer 1 mental trauma. Each investigator begins the next scenario with 2 fewer cards in their starting hand."
msgstr "在剧本日志中，“吾家可归”下记录2进展并承受1点精神创伤。每位调查员少2张起始手牌开始下一场冒险。"

msgid "Put the Barrier Core into play, <i>(Inactive)</i> side faceup."
msgstr "将屏障核心放置入场，<i>（未激活）</i>面朝上。"

msgid "Gather each Sea Floor location and remove one copy of Coral Reef and one copy of Drowned Acropolis from the game at random."
msgstr "收齐每个海床地点，将随机一张珊瑚礁和随机一张溺亡卫城从游戏中移除。"

msgid "Shuffle the eight remaining Sea Floor locations together and put them into play in a 3x3 grid around the Barrier Core as shown in the location placement diagram."
msgstr "混洗剩余的8张海床地点，按照右侧的地点摆放示意图，放置入场，呈3x3的方阵，屏障核心位于中间。"

msgid "Each investigator begins play at the Barrier Core."
msgstr "每位调查员从屏障核心开始游戏。"

msgid "Sea Floor"
msgstr "海床"

msgid "Barrier Core"
msgstr "屏障核心"

msgid "Set the Barrier Node story asset and the double-sided Undersea Parasite [tdc_rune_x] and Obsidian Relic [tdc_rune_y] cards aside, out of play."
msgstr "将屏障节点剧情支援、双面的海底寄生虫[tdc_rune_x]和黑曜石遗物[tdc_rune_y]卡牌放在一边，位于场外。"

msgid "Add the flood tokens to the token pool and check your Campaign Log:"
msgstr "将淹没标记加入供应堆并检查你的剧本日志："

msgid "The rising city has shaken the ancient dome. Increase the flood level of 1 [per_investigator] Sea Floor locations."
msgstr "升起的古城撼动了远古的穹顶。提升1[per_investigator]个海床地点的淹没等级。"

msgid "During this scenario, locations are arranged in a set grid pattern. <b>Each location is connected to each location adjacent to it.</b>"
msgstr "本场冒险期间，地点排列成一组方阵。<b>每个地点与其相邻的每个地点连接。</b>"

msgid "Your failure has distracted you from your goals. Each investigator must erase 1 progress under their Task, if able."
msgstr "你的失败让你远离了目标。如可能，每位调查员必须擦去其任务的1进展。"

msgid "Check the box next to \"Barrier Node\" under \"Artifacts Earned.\""
msgstr "在剧本日志“取得的神器”部分，“屏障节点”旁的方框内打勾。"

msgid "Barrier Node"
msgstr "屏障节点"

msgid "the power was diverted."
msgstr "能源已经转移。"

msgid "Each investigator earns 2 bonus experience from studying the Drowned Quarter at length."
msgstr "每位调查员取得2点奖励经验值，因其充分研究了溺亡城区。"

msgid "In your Campaign Log, cross out \"The Drowned Quarter\" on the R'lyeh map."
msgstr "在剧本日志中，拉莱耶地图的部分划掉“溺亡城区”。"

msgid "On the other side of the dome entrance, you look through the gossamer barrier to the ocean floor. The ocean reclaimed the alien dome in mere seconds. It is a minor miracle that you weren’t swept away."
msgstr "你在穹顶入口的一侧，透过薄纱一般的屏障看到了海底。海洋在几秒之内就夺回了这座异星的穹顶。你们没被卷走真是个小小的奇迹。"

msgid "The strange node pulses in your hand, projecting a soft bubble of light that repels the falling debris. You make it to the entrance as the dome bursts like a bubble. The expedition looks on in a mixture of awe and fear as a torrent of seawater reclaims the alien structure. A small prick of pain shoots through your palm, and you look down to see the node bury itself in your palm, sending spidery black hairs radiating out under your skin. They retract painlessly when you pull the node away. Tillinghast will certainly be pleased with this find."
msgstr "奇异的节点在你手中搏动，射出柔和的光泡泡，推开了坠落的碎骸。就在穹顶也像泡泡一样碎裂的时候，你来到了入口。海水狂潮夺回了异星建筑，探险队看着，又是敬畏，又是害怕。你掌心传来细微的刺痛。你低头看去，发现节点已经埋入你的掌心，在皮肤下面长出蜘蛛状的黑色毛发。你拿开节点，毛发就收缩起来，一点儿也不疼。蒂林哈斯特肯定乐于见到这一发现。"

msgid "The reactivated core makes quick work of the flooded dome, draining the water in mere minutes. You survey the perimeter of the sunken ruin with the expedition, marveling at its ancient grandeur. The feeling of walking on a dry ocean floor, with fish flitting beyond the flickering bubble, is like something out of a dream. After several hours, the expedition presses on."
msgstr "重新激活的核心在几分钟之内就把淹没的穹顶内的积水抽取干净。你和探险队一起勘察沉没遗迹的四周，惊叹着远古的恢弘。你走在干爽的海底，海鱼在发光的泡泡上掠过，这幅景象真是如梦似幻。几小时后，探险队就继续前进了。"

msgid "The energy field protecting the tunnel back to the city continues to hold strong. The jagged foundations of R’lyeh continue to break off in pieces as the city rises. It is time to move on."
msgstr "保护返回城市隧道的能量场依然坚挺。拉莱耶还在升起，它参差的基座也还在落下碎块。是时候继续前进了。"
